Bring a #medium pot{} of @water{} and @salt{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}(quartered).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, scallion whites, and @shelled edamame{4%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%ounce}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} into pan with veggies; bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium low.

Once water is boiling, add half the @ramen noodles{6%ounce} (all for 4 servings) to #pot{}. Cook until tender, ~{60%seconds}.

> Noodles overcook quickly; don't cook more than 60 seconds!

Drain and rinse thoroughly under cold water, at least ~{30%seconds}. (This stops the cooking and helps prevent sticky noodles.)

Add drained noodles to pan with veggies and toss to combine; cook, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If sauce is too thick, add a splash of water.

Remove from heat. Stir in juice from two lime wedges (whole lime for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide noodle stir-fry between #bowls{}. Garnish with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.